I have gotten a lot of questions on what I had done at @solacemed && many of them are why did I do anything so… let me address that first. 
I know I already had full lips but, when I smile my top lip disappears so Mrs. Shannon did two things, she did just a tiny bit of Botox right under each side of my nose, that helped relaxed that muscle && then did a little filler in my lips to help give them more of a shade && also some plump😉 She also put filler in my chin && I love the way it enhanced my profile. 
I wouldn’t just do this with anyone but, I have known Mrs. Shannon my whole life && I completely trusted her opinion && skill to make it look natural. 
NONE OF IT HURT! 
The @solacemed offers so many health && beauty services && they are expanding! 
&& If you are looking for a Mother’s Day gift, you should  check out the @solace.boutiquetx 
I hope to be showing y’all some more of that soon. 
Hope you are having a blessed Sunday! 
XOXO Mills…

2023 you’ve been a hard one…

This year has taught me the most out of all so far. You’ve taught me how to navigate relationships, things I needed to let go of that were bad for me, struggles && pain. 
But, what you brought me was finding true friendships, accomplishments that I never thought I was capable of, strength, love, true happiness && the best lesson I have learned this year is being 100% my true self. ✨

The start of 2023 until about August was a huge struggle for me, so many things changed && I had to let go of a lot of things that have been in my life for years && honestly, I never thought of eliminating them because if you know me, I don’t give up easily on anything…

By pushing out the negative && nurturing all the good in my life was a game changer!  I know being in your 20’s are all about “lessons” but not enough people talk about the struggles it brings. Most people wanna talk about the rainbows && sunshine but, it truly is a hard battle from finding your passion, to loving your true self to learning who you really are && not being what everyone else wants or says your are at this age. It’s hard!! 

I know the biggest battle for me this year was self love (I’m still working on it) being able to love myself && being okay with being different && not fitting in with a lot of people I really wanted to. 

 Another thing was holding on to friendships that needed to be let go of && that were one sided. This was extremely hard for me because, I want to be friends with everyone even when they aren’t meant for me && I finally learned that God brings in people for a season to teach you && sometimes need to be loved from a distance.

I know God had me wait for my right people && this year God has shown me those people more than ever && it’s something I am beyond grateful for EVERYDAY SINGLE DAY!
He has placed people in my life that push me when I need to be pushed && tells me to rest when I need to rest && simply just love me for me.🩷

2023 thank you for the happiness ☺️
2024 I’m ready for what you have to bring me!
